Financial Credit-Default Swap Indexes Surge to Records in Europe

-- B y   M i c h a e l   S h a n a h a n
-- 
2011-08-22T07:11:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-22/financial-credit-default-swap-indexes-surge-to-records-in-europe.html
The cost of insuring bank bonds
surged to records in  Europe , according to traders of credit-
default swaps.  Contracts on the Markit iTraxx Financial Index linked to
senior debt of 25 banks and insurers climbed 13.5 basis points
to 248.5 basis points, the highest-ever level based on closing
prices, according to JPMorgan Chase & Co. at 8 a.m. in  London .
The subordinated financial bond index was up 33 at a record
442.5.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Shanahan at 
 mshanahan3@bloomberg.net  